<http://drug.uk/usage/pregnancy/4ae90fec-b291-4245-9b9a-a730b90324fd> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> " An increased risk of major congenital malformations has been seen with carbamazepine.\nMonitoring in pregnancy\nPlasma-drug concentration should be monitored and may be maintained on the lower side of the therapeutic range provided seizure control is maintained." .
